Sec. 201.020. RECORDS; HEARINGS; RULES. (a) The state board
shall keep a complete record of all of its official actions, may hold
public hearings at times and places in this state as determined by
the board, and may adopt rules as necessary for the performance of
its functions under this chapter.
(b) The state board shall develop and implement policies which
will provide the public with a reasonable opportunity to appear
before the board and to speak on any issue under the jurisdiction of
the board.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1463, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.
Amended by Acts 1985, 69th Leg., ch. 611, Sec. 15, eff. Sept. 1,
1985.

Statute text rendered on: 8/6/2022

